1
00:00:08,521 --> 00:00:10,521
[insects chirping softly]

2
00:00:14,729 --> 00:00:16,479
[cat meowing in background]

3
00:00:23,562 --> 00:00:24,687
Margot?

4
00:00:25,771 --> 00:00:27,187
Margot, it's me.

5
00:00:28,562 --> 00:00:29,687
[metal clangs]

6
00:00:31,187 --> 00:00:32,437
What's she doing?

7
00:00:38,229 --> 00:00:40,229
[door unlocking]

8
00:00:42,604 --> 00:00:44,354
Are you kidding? It's four in the morning.

9
00:00:46,104 --> 00:00:47,437
[sighs]

10
00:00:49,146 --> 00:00:50,729
[Margot] Is that coming inside?

11
00:00:51,437 --> 00:00:52,646
Just for a little.

12
00:00:53,812 --> 00:00:55,521
[breathes deeply]

13
00:00:56,021 --> 00:00:58,521
- How much?
- At least 30 kilos.

14
00:01:02,146 --> 00:01:03,104
Let's go.

15
00:01:14,229 --> 00:01:16,229
You can put two of them in there.

16
00:01:18,437 --> 00:01:19,687
[plates clatter]

17
00:01:24,396 --> 00:01:26,312
[sucks teeth] It's cool, we got it.

18
00:01:26,396 --> 00:01:27,479
It's all right.

19
00:01:28,104 --> 00:01:29,271
Go to bed.

20
00:01:35,354 --> 00:01:36,354
Here.

21
00:01:37,812 --> 00:01:38,937
Be careful.

22
00:01:40,187 --> 00:01:41,646
Look after yourselves.

23
00:01:43,062 --> 00:01:45,146
- We will.
- [Kingsley] We got this.

24
00:02:06,437 --> 00:02:07,812
LEGAL NOTICE

25
00:02:11,104 --> 00:02:13,646
LEGAL NOTICE

26
00:02:13,729 --> 00:02:15,062
[Margot sighs]

27
00:02:26,896 --> 00:02:29,437
THE PAYMENT OF 350 EUROS OWED
CONCERNING A 125 CC SCOOTER

28
00:02:29,521 --> 00:02:31,062
WE STILL HAVE NOT RECEIVED PAYMENT

29
00:02:31,146 --> 00:02:33,104
IF PAYMENT IS NOT RECEIVED
WITHIN THREE DAYS

30
00:02:33,187 --> 00:02:34,187
GARNISH YOUR WAGES

31
00:02:46,354 --> 00:02:47,937
I've been thinking.

32
00:02:48,646 --> 00:02:51,604
Now that we know each other,
you can carry shit for me.

33
00:02:51,687 --> 00:02:53,604
- Are you for fucking real?
- [laughs]

34
00:02:53,687 --> 00:02:57,062
Hey, how many times do we have
to sleep together for you to help me?

35
00:02:57,646 --> 00:02:59,396
[chuckles] I may have some friends.

36
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:00,479
[Kingsley] Hmm…

37
00:03:00,562 --> 00:03:01,687
Measurements?

38
00:03:02,854 --> 00:03:04,812
- Out of your league.
- Pfft.

39
00:03:05,312 --> 00:03:07,896
I'll introduce you to one,
but I'm taking 10%.

40
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:10,396
Mmm-mmm. That's damn greedy.

41
00:03:12,646 --> 00:03:15,646
["Rosalie" by Ayewai & DJ Skyro playing]

42
00:03:19,354 --> 00:03:22,354
[sensual song continues]

43
00:03:48,146 --> 00:03:49,521
Give a little package deal?

44
00:03:50,604 --> 00:03:51,979
Mmm-mmm.

45
00:03:56,062 --> 00:03:58,062
[espresso machine whirring]

46
00:03:58,979 --> 00:04:00,062
So who knew?

47
00:04:01,229 --> 00:04:02,479
Just my guys.

48
00:04:03,396 --> 00:04:04,646
And my guys never talk.

49
00:04:18,729 --> 00:04:20,312
[sighs heavily]

50
00:04:24,854 --> 00:04:27,021
Kingsley Lafleur, that son of a…

51
00:04:28,187 --> 00:04:29,604
How did he know?

52
00:04:32,396 --> 00:04:34,396
The Lafleurs are pissing me off.

53
00:04:34,937 --> 00:04:36,771
And I expect you can fix it?

54
00:04:38,437 --> 00:04:39,604
Tell me if I'm wrong.

55
00:04:40,521 --> 00:04:42,062
Don't worry, I'll fix it.

56
00:04:45,396 --> 00:04:47,104
I'm gonna… [sighs]

57
00:04:48,937 --> 00:04:50,937
[plane engine roaring]

58
00:05:07,771 --> 00:05:08,771
Where's my sister?

59
00:05:08,854 --> 00:05:10,312
A sauna in Paris.

60
00:05:25,271 --> 00:05:26,271
Pépé!

61
00:06:11,812 --> 00:06:14,812
- Can we be serious now?
- [darkly intriguing music playing]

62
00:06:36,854 --> 00:06:38,021
[Marco] Pick one.

63
00:06:40,021 --> 00:06:43,646
For a ton,
it's 500,000 upfront and a deposit.

64
00:06:44,396 --> 00:06:47,396
We'll take care of him,
unless you fuck us over.

65
00:06:47,479 --> 00:06:51,937
In which case, you'll get your deposit
returned in small installments.

66
00:06:56,146 --> 00:06:57,562
Why you pick the young ones?

67
00:06:58,354 --> 00:07:01,271
We prefer fresh fruit. Nothing rotten.

68
00:07:03,437 --> 00:07:06,771
Once we get the money and the deposit,
the shipment will head out.

69
00:07:06,854 --> 00:07:09,854
- [Pépé whistles]
- [darkly intriguing music continues]

70
00:07:31,021 --> 00:07:32,271
It's too bad.

71
00:07:32,812 --> 00:07:36,729
You could have given King or Annabelle,
but he prefers fresh fruit.

72
00:07:37,687 --> 00:07:38,771
Watch what you say to me.

73
00:07:40,062 --> 00:07:42,896
The whole trip almost got fucked up,
all because of her.

74
00:07:42,979 --> 00:07:46,896
Okay, it was a mistake sending her over,
I'll admit it, but she knew Xhésus.

75
00:07:46,979 --> 00:07:49,062
Oh, they're pretty close, it seems.

76
00:07:49,146 --> 00:07:51,396
In fact, she's getting to know him
damn well right now.

77
00:07:55,271 --> 00:07:58,187
We do this one, we make bank,
and then we're over.

78
00:08:02,687 --> 00:08:04,062
Everyone's got their shit.

79
00:08:04,146 --> 00:08:05,521
Yours is your family.

80
00:08:05,604 --> 00:08:07,562
But it's not mine. It's too dangerous.

81
00:08:10,562 --> 00:08:13,562
["Luffy" by J Kevlar playing]

82
00:08:19,021 --> 00:08:22,521
[dramatic rap song continues]

83
00:08:36,396 --> 00:08:38,021
- [song fades]
- [chimes]

84
00:08:38,104 --> 00:08:40,229
YOU'VE JUST RECEIVED 2.85 BTC

85
00:08:42,479 --> 00:08:43,896
Bravo, Putin.

86
00:08:45,687 --> 00:08:47,146
I've got one ton coming soon.

87
00:08:49,979 --> 00:08:51,646
One ton. That's pretty good.

88
00:08:52,354 --> 00:08:53,604
Can I still count on you?

89
00:08:57,729 --> 00:09:00,312
Someone robbed a boat
yesterday at the Marin.

90
00:09:01,687 --> 00:09:03,979
- You hear about it?
- No.

91
00:09:04,854 --> 00:09:06,354
It belongs to Alex Croquet.

92
00:09:08,187 --> 00:09:09,604
What was on the boat?

93
00:09:11,062 --> 00:09:12,187
Who knows?

94
00:09:13,354 --> 00:09:15,771
This smells like Kingsley Lafleur.

95
00:09:16,896 --> 00:09:19,187
Why would he butt in? Why is he involved?

96
00:09:19,687 --> 00:09:20,979
I'm not sure.

97
00:09:22,812 --> 00:09:24,521
You with me? That's all I need to know.

98
00:09:25,104 --> 00:09:26,104
Hell yeah.

99
00:09:27,104 --> 00:09:30,354
But this ain't kid shit. They're tough.

100
00:09:31,521 --> 00:09:35,437
And tough guys will cut off your arm
if there's dead weight attached to it.

101
00:09:36,312 --> 00:09:37,979
Think you're tough enough?

102
00:09:39,562 --> 00:09:42,937
I've always handled it.
So I'll handle this. Got it?

103
00:09:55,521 --> 00:09:58,271
[Chloé] Can we make an appointment?
Could we…

104
00:10:00,146 --> 00:10:03,104
Yes, I understand
what you're telling me, but…

105
00:10:03,687 --> 00:10:05,979
Yes, I know it's been a week, but listen…

106
00:10:07,062 --> 00:10:08,104
Yes.

107
00:10:09,812 --> 00:10:12,937
We'll figure something out. Yes.

108
00:10:15,021 --> 00:10:16,146
Chloé?

109
00:10:16,937 --> 00:10:18,104
[Chloé] Yes, I know.

110
00:10:18,687 --> 00:10:21,354
- We'll review the explanation page.
- Chloé?

111
00:10:21,854 --> 00:10:24,104
Yeah, it's been picking up, though.

112
00:10:24,187 --> 00:10:26,687
[man on phone] I looked
at your crowdfunding page.

113
00:10:26,771 --> 00:10:28,271
It's still insufficient.

114
00:10:28,354 --> 00:10:30,896
- Who's on the phone?
- We got refused by the bank.

115
00:10:32,604 --> 00:10:35,479
- Hey, let me. Give him to me.
- Yes. Yes, I know, but--

116
00:10:35,562 --> 00:10:36,562
Hello?

117
00:10:37,062 --> 00:10:39,687
- [man] Mr. Lafleur?
- You're refusing the loan?

118
00:10:40,187 --> 00:10:43,479
That's what I was telling your partner.
You don't have the down payment.

119
00:10:43,562 --> 00:10:44,646
We're gettin' it.

120
00:10:44,729 --> 00:10:48,479
I looked at your crowdfunding page,
and you've only raised 120 euros.

121
00:10:48,562 --> 00:10:50,146
We need at least 15 grand.

122
00:10:50,229 --> 00:10:51,562
It's going up, though.

123
00:10:51,646 --> 00:10:54,021
That may be, but right now
my hands are tied.

124
00:10:54,104 --> 00:10:57,104
When you hit 15K, let me know,
but until then, I'm sorry.

125
00:10:57,187 --> 00:10:59,396
Look, we really need this.
I'm begging you.

126
00:10:59,896 --> 00:11:01,896
I understand,
but there's nothing I can do.

127
00:11:01,979 --> 00:11:04,687
I've already had my supervisor
look at your application.

128
00:11:04,771 --> 00:11:06,937
Listen, my house burned down,
it needs repairs.

129
00:11:07,021 --> 00:11:09,479
My siblings gotta have
a roof over their heads.

130
00:11:09,562 --> 00:11:10,937
What about a personal bank loan?

131
00:11:11,521 --> 00:11:13,021
I'm really sorry, Mr. Lafleur.

132
00:11:13,104 --> 00:11:15,687
We only grant business loans
for specific projects.

133
00:11:15,771 --> 00:11:17,146
Come on, please!

134
00:11:17,646 --> 00:11:19,021
I'm sorry, Mr. Lafleur.

135
00:11:20,104 --> 00:11:21,771
You've talked to my friend, Chloé, yeah?

136
00:11:22,437 --> 00:11:24,771
Uh, yes, when you came into the office.

137
00:11:24,854 --> 00:11:27,437
- Are you interested in her?
- Um…

138
00:11:27,521 --> 00:11:29,312
- She'll suck you if you want.
- What? Marvin!

139
00:11:29,396 --> 00:11:31,562
- [man] Wait--
- You prefer men? Then I can suck you.

140
00:11:31,646 --> 00:11:32,604
- Marvin.
- [man] Sir…

141
00:11:32,687 --> 00:11:35,104
[angrily] What the fuck
do you want from us, huh?

142
00:11:35,604 --> 00:11:37,146
Motherfucking cunt!

143
00:11:37,229 --> 00:11:39,937
- Whoa! You're messed up in the head.
- God damn it!

144
00:11:41,354 --> 00:11:42,437
[door slams]

145
00:11:42,521 --> 00:11:44,521
[somber music playing]

146
00:12:03,812 --> 00:12:05,521
We're not gonna make it.

147
00:12:05,604 --> 00:12:07,146
Come on.

148
00:12:07,229 --> 00:12:08,229
[sucks teeth]

149
00:12:09,271 --> 00:12:12,812
It was crazy to think we would manage
to keep everyone together like before.

150
00:12:12,896 --> 00:12:14,312
It was Mama who did that.

151
00:12:14,396 --> 00:12:16,521
We can't leave them with Aunt Régine.

152
00:12:16,604 --> 00:12:18,271
What do you want us to do, Ambre?

153
00:12:19,312 --> 00:12:21,021
There's my music, your app.

154
00:12:21,104 --> 00:12:22,854
My app is stupid.

155
00:12:23,479 --> 00:12:25,854
But we still gotta hold on to some faith.

156
00:12:26,604 --> 00:12:28,229
King and Kylian were actually right.

157
00:12:29,812 --> 00:12:31,062
Hang on, are you serious?

158
00:12:31,854 --> 00:12:33,437
We don't have a choice, not really.

159
00:12:34,687 --> 00:12:37,729
I'm making a choice.
But I need you to stay strong.

160
00:12:38,687 --> 00:12:41,312
Marvin, look at you. You've got muscles.

161
00:12:41,396 --> 00:12:42,562
You're tough.

162
00:12:42,646 --> 00:12:44,021
Where is your strength?

163
00:12:44,604 --> 00:12:46,354
You're like our father.

164
00:12:46,437 --> 00:12:47,562
You flinch, it's over.

165
00:12:52,562 --> 00:12:53,979
I never flinch.

166
00:12:55,396 --> 00:12:56,562
Well, good.

167
00:12:57,812 --> 00:12:59,271
I gotta go to work.

168
00:13:13,521 --> 00:13:14,521
So what's your plan?

169
00:13:22,146 --> 00:13:25,229
Soon, I'll earn enough
to provide for everyone for many years.

170
00:13:27,396 --> 00:13:29,021
- When?
- A month.

171
00:13:29,896 --> 00:13:33,187
Till then, I'll give you the money
to fix the house back up.

172
00:13:33,271 --> 00:13:34,396
What money?

173
00:13:34,479 --> 00:13:35,687
I have it.

174
00:13:35,771 --> 00:13:38,521
I'll have to launder it, though.
How about that app of yours?

175
00:13:40,562 --> 00:13:41,979
The app will hold the money?

176
00:13:42,562 --> 00:13:44,354
You're gonna get plenty of clients.

177
00:13:44,437 --> 00:13:46,021
More than you think you will.

178
00:13:46,104 --> 00:13:47,771
The clients will pay you in cash.

179
00:13:48,271 --> 00:13:50,562
It'll be entered into your account
and into the books.

180
00:13:51,729 --> 00:13:53,229
Then you can help us.

181
00:13:54,937 --> 00:13:57,437
[sighs] How have you fallen this low?

182
00:13:57,937 --> 00:13:59,062
[sighs]

183
00:14:00,646 --> 00:14:04,021
Didn't have a choice.
I need more than survival.

184
00:14:05,229 --> 00:14:07,146
I don't want to be disrespected.

185
00:14:08,062 --> 00:14:09,479
I'm done being kicked down.

186
00:14:09,562 --> 00:14:12,896
I'm not ending up like Dad,
and especially not like Dark.

187
00:14:12,979 --> 00:14:14,562
I'm not gonna work my ass off

188
00:14:14,646 --> 00:14:17,437
but still get my kids
placed in goddamn foster care.

189
00:14:17,937 --> 00:14:21,229
You remember how hard our Ma worked?
And look at us now.

190
00:14:22,437 --> 00:14:24,312
This job will give us a windfall.

191
00:14:24,396 --> 00:14:25,937
After, we'll stop.

192
00:14:26,729 --> 00:14:27,854
Swear it.

193
00:14:29,521 --> 00:14:30,521
I swear it.

194
00:14:31,896 --> 00:14:34,146
- Chloé can never find out.
- [Pearl laughs]

195
00:14:35,687 --> 00:14:36,896
What's so funny?

196
00:14:36,979 --> 00:14:38,271
Mmm, nothing.

197
00:14:38,354 --> 00:14:40,021
Tell me, I'm interested.

198
00:14:40,104 --> 00:14:41,146
Let it go, Marv.

199
00:14:41,771 --> 00:14:43,979
Your girl is gonna find out eventually.

200
00:14:44,854 --> 00:14:46,771
If it's only once, she won't find out.

201
00:14:48,271 --> 00:14:49,437
Just this once.

202
00:14:56,562 --> 00:14:57,979
I'm really glad you came.

203
00:14:59,937 --> 00:15:00,937
Yeah.

204
00:15:02,187 --> 00:15:05,104
- Know where King was last night?
- I don't know, why?

205
00:15:07,271 --> 00:15:08,479
Can you find out for me?

206
00:15:11,812 --> 00:15:13,104
Yeah, I'll try.

207
00:15:15,437 --> 00:15:17,437
[indistinct chatter]

208
00:15:22,396 --> 00:15:25,229
Twenty grams per liter of water.
Drink it during the day.

209
00:15:25,312 --> 00:15:28,312
Mmm. Thank God you're here.
This menopause is killing me.

210
00:15:28,396 --> 00:15:29,604
- Thank you.
- Here.

211
00:15:29,687 --> 00:15:30,979
And how's home?

212
00:15:31,062 --> 00:15:32,979
- We're doin' okay.
- Chin up, my dear.

213
00:15:33,062 --> 00:15:35,937
- All right? Take care.
- Thank you. Yeah. You too, see you.

214
00:15:43,271 --> 00:15:45,271
[scooter approaching]

215
00:15:46,896 --> 00:15:49,896
- [chatter continues]
- [menacing music playing]

216
00:16:04,104 --> 00:16:06,729
- [woman] Need any help?
- [SherKhan] Where's the Lafleur stand?

217
00:16:06,812 --> 00:16:09,312
- [woman] Uh, it's right over there.
- [SherKhan] Thanks.

218
00:16:09,896 --> 00:16:12,312
- Oh shit.
- [menacing music continues]

219
00:16:31,146 --> 00:16:34,562
Ah! You were at the hospital,
little idiot. Where's your brother?

220
00:16:36,229 --> 00:16:38,437
- Tell me!
- Uh, which brother?

221
00:16:38,521 --> 00:16:40,854
God, how many you got in your family?
Kingsley!

222
00:16:41,437 --> 00:16:42,812
I don't know who that is.

223
00:16:42,896 --> 00:16:44,937
Seriously? You want me to rough you up?

224
00:16:45,021 --> 00:16:47,687
He's not at home.
He left when our mother died.

225
00:16:48,979 --> 00:16:50,354
It's true, I'm not lying.

226
00:16:51,437 --> 00:16:54,521
- [man] Hey! What are you doing?
- [woman] Miss, do you know that man?

227
00:16:54,604 --> 00:16:56,854
- Do you need help?
- [man] Back off, man. Get away.

228
00:16:57,396 --> 00:17:00,187
Listen here. You're gonna
give a message to that imbecile.

229
00:17:01,146 --> 00:17:04,604
"Bring back what he stole
or I'll cut him up like a pig."

230
00:17:06,021 --> 00:17:08,187
- Let me go! That hurts!
- [crowd exclaiming]

231
00:17:08,271 --> 00:17:10,021
[crowd muttering]

232
00:17:21,146 --> 00:17:23,146
[suspenseful music playing]

233
00:18:25,937 --> 00:18:27,729
- [Kingsley] Shh! Shh!
- Ahh!

234
00:18:29,146 --> 00:18:31,729
- Don't worry, ma'am. Don't move.
- [muffled grunting]

235
00:18:35,146 --> 00:18:37,312
- [muffled grunting continues]
- Quiet! Shh!

236
00:18:39,896 --> 00:18:42,312
Tell Jérôme
that Robin fucking Hood did this.

237
00:18:42,812 --> 00:18:44,812
[muffled grunting continues]

238
00:18:57,521 --> 00:18:59,521
[bell ringing]

239
00:19:03,896 --> 00:19:05,271
- [woman] Goodbye.
- Bye.

240
00:19:05,354 --> 00:19:06,354
Mr. Novilo?

241
00:19:08,812 --> 00:19:10,146
Hello.

242
00:19:10,937 --> 00:19:11,979
[door closes]

243
00:19:13,979 --> 00:19:16,271
Is this the place to file for bankruptcy?

244
00:19:16,354 --> 00:19:18,604
Yes, but there's a wait. Have a seat.

245
00:19:18,687 --> 00:19:19,687
Okay.

246
00:19:31,062 --> 00:19:33,771
I think it's safe to say you'll be fine.

247
00:19:33,854 --> 00:19:36,729
- Your first time?
- Yeah, but one debt is enough, right?

248
00:19:37,771 --> 00:19:40,187
So true. So true.

249
00:19:45,729 --> 00:19:47,146
What should I expect from this?

250
00:19:47,812 --> 00:19:50,104
Well, they'll poke through
your whole life.

251
00:19:50,687 --> 00:19:54,896
How much goes towards your nails,
if you show up to work regularly or not,

252
00:19:55,604 --> 00:19:57,979
If you have a great-aunt
who can lend you money.

253
00:19:58,687 --> 00:20:01,187
Don't worry, hon,
they won't be too hard on you.

254
